      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It can be incredibly disheartening to feel like no medical treatment is providing relief. Considering that you've already seen multiple doctors, it may be helpful to explore alternative options, such as pain management clinics or specialists with experience in chronic pain. Additionally, reaching out to support groups or online communities focused on chronic pain can connect you with others who may be able to offer empathy and understanding. Sometimes, just sharing your experience can help you feel less isolated.",
      "source": "target",
